		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">At 14th level, you learn the Litany of Flame. To use it, you must spend a use of your Wild Shape and an action. Once it has begun, you must concentrate on it like a spell, and you may keep it active for up to 10 minutes. While the Litany of Flame is active you gain the following effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You continuously chant the Litany, precluding you from casting spells.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain immunity to fire damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You shed bright light in a 50-foot radius around you and dim light a further 50 feet beyond that. The light is considered daylight.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain unlimited use of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.brs5ieevwfasrb6u]{Brand of Flame}.&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain the benefits of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.hm481xz98jml7nbb]{Eyes of Piercing Flame}.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">As an action you may cause a creature within 30 feet of you to ignite, taking 3d6 fire damage and 1d6 ongoing fire damage. A creature may spend an action to put the fire out, ending the ongoing damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">As a bonus action, you may ignite a 10-foot square into flames, within 30 feet of you. It is affected as per the Fire encounter element.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">As a reaction, you may cause a creature within 60 feet of you whose presence you are aware of to be outlined in ghostly flames as if it were affected by @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.z7r6plq6vyesck07]{Faerie Fire}. If you stop chanting or lose concentration, the effect ends.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
